Here are both approaches for navigating from a `CollectionView` tap to `ProductDetailsPage`.

## 1. Register the route

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

**Approach A — String query parameter (product ID only):**

```csharp
// ProductListViewModel.cs
[RelayCommand]
async Task ProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?id={product.Id}");
}
```

**Approach B — Pass the full object via `ShellNavigationQueryParameters`:**

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
async Task ProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Wire the CollectionView tap

```xml
<!-- ProductListPage.xaml -->
<CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Products}"
                SelectionMode="Single"
                SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ProductSelectedCommand}"
                SelectionChangedCommandParameter="{Binding SelectedItem,
                    Source={RelativeSource Self}}">
    <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Product">
            <VerticalStackLayout Padding="10">
                <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="18" />
                <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
            </VerticalStackLayout>
        </DataTemplate>
    </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
</CollectionView>
```

## 4. Receive data with `IQueryAttributable`

```csharp
// ProductDetailsViewModel.cs
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    string productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    Product product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string ID passed via query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("id", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using ProductId
        }

        // Approach B: full object passed via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions.
- String query params are best for simple IDs and deep-link support.
- `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` avoids serialization but doesn't support deep links.
- `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel handles both approaches in one place and is preferred over `[QueryProperty]` on the page.
